{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_4","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"for f in task-plans/*.md; do echo '---'; echo \\\"\"'$f\"; sed -n '\"'1,24p' \\\"\"'$f\"; done'","aggregated_output":"---\ntask-plans/board-interaction-quality-task-plan.md\n# Board Interaction Quality Task Plan\n\nStatus: complete\n\n## Priority\n\nPriority 1\n\n## Objective\n\nMake the board stable, predictable, and smooth enough for daily use.\n\n## Why This Matters\n\nThe board is the main operating surface. If drag, resize, and card-density rules are unstable, the rest of the extension feels unreliable.\n\n## Scope\n\n- drag placement reliability\n- resize reliability in all supported directions\n- drop overlay correctness and smoothness\n- `T / S / M / L` density rules\n- `Needs Human` occupancy rules\n- board-only interaction rules\n---\ntask-plans/claude-codex-team-space-task-plan.md\n# Claude Codex Team Space Task Plan\n\n## Priority\n\nPriority 3\n\n## Objective\n\nExpand from Codex-only control into a provider-aware agent team workspace.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Claude + Codex shared board\n- provider-aware role separation\n- collaboration model across providers\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Task 1 — Provider Abstraction\n\n- define provider-neutral thread/task concepts\n- keep provider-specific actions isolated\n\n### Task 2 — Shared Team Surface\n---\ntask-plans/cma-codex-communication-optimization-task-plan.md\n# CMA Codex Communication Optimization Task Plan\n\nStatus: planned\n\n## Priority\n\nPriority 1\n\n## Objective\n\nReduce control latency and make Codex interaction feel immediate inside `Codex-Managed-Agent`.\n\n## Scope\n\n- optimistic `sendPrompt` and `auto-continue` feedback\n- lightweight Codex tab link-state synchronization\n- fewer full refreshes and fewer full rerenders for small actions\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Task 1 — Optimistic Queued State\n\n- [ ] show `queued` immediately after `sendPrompt`\n- [ ] show `queued` immediately after `auto-continue` is armed or triggered\n---\ntask-plans/codex-loop-control-surface-task-plan.md\n# Codex Loop Control Surface Task Plan\n\nStatus: planned\n\n## Priority\n\nPriority 1\n\n## Objective\n\nExpose `codex-loop` as a first-class managed surface inside `Codex-Managed-Agent` instead of leaving daemon control in shell scripts only.\n\n## Scope\n\n- daemon status inside the extension\n- watch / tail visibility for loop logs\n- card-level loop enablement\n- interval presets such as `10 min`, `20 min`, and custom input\n- quick start / stop / restart controls\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Task 1 — Loop Status Visibility\n\n---\ntask-plans/codex-multi-agent-coordination-task-plan.md\n# Codex Multi-Agent Coordination Task Plan\n\n## Priority\n\nPriority 3\n\n## Objective\n\nSupport deliberate collaboration across multiple Codex threads.\n\n## Scope\n\n- multi-thread work planning\n- ownership and baton passing\n- coordination surfaces\n- team-state visibility\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Task 1 — Coordination Model\n\n- define how work is assigned between threads\n- define what counts as ownership, handoff, and waiting\n\n---\ntask-plans/codex-visibility-control-task-plan.md\n# Codex Visibility Control Task Plan\n\nStatus: complete\n\n## Priority\n\nPriority 1\n\n## Objective\n\nGive the user deliberate control over whether a thread is surfaced in the official Codex experience.\n\n## Scope\n\n- `Show in Codex`\n- `Hide from Codex`\n- archive/unarchive handling\n- name sync\n- open target thread in Codex\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Task 1 — Show in Codex\n\n---\ntask-plans/cross-path-unified-management-task-plan.md\n# Cross-Path Unified Management Task Plan\n\n## Priority\n\nPriority 1\n\n## Objective\n\nManage threads across multiple project roots from one control surface.\n\n## Scope\n\n- cross-path discovery\n- path-aware grouping and filtering\n- board actions across roots\n- remove the need for one project per VS Code window\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Task 1 — Path Model\n\n- normalize cwd/workspace paths\n- group threads by root or project identity\n- make path origin visible but compact\n---\ntask-plans/html-ppt-visual-extensions-task-plan.md\n# HTML PPT Visual Extensions Task Plan\n\n## Priority\n\nPriority 4\n\n## Objective\n\nAdd presentation and visual-output tooling without destabilizing the core Agent Center.\n\n## Scope\n\n- HTML/PPT workflow support\n- icon/theme expansion\n- presentation-oriented outputs\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Task 1 — Presentation Workflow Definition\n\n- define what HTML/PPT generation actually needs from the agent center\n- separate presentational tooling from core control logic\n\n### Task 2 — Visual System Extensions\n---\ntask-plans/insight-and-guidance-task-plan.md\n# Insight and Guidance Task Plan\n\nStatus: complete\n\n## Priority\n\nPriority 2\n\n## Objective\n\nMake insights actionable, persistent, and connected to real workflow changes.\n\n## Scope\n\n- usage report quality\n- topic map actions\n- word cloud usefulness\n- weekly shift guidance\n- vibe-coding advice\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Task 1 — Insight Persistence\n\n---\ntask-plans/no-editor-first-workflows-task-plan.md\n# No Editor First Workflows Task Plan\n\nStatus: complete\n\n## Priority\n\nPriority 2\n\n## Objective\n\nMake the managed center the default place for routine agent operations.\n\n## Scope\n\n- send prompt from cards\n- loop control from cards\n- inspect without opening extra surfaces\n- log/result visibility inside cards and drawer\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Task 1 — Card-Level Operations\n\n- [x] keep prompt send, Codex jump, and loop actions usable from board cards\n---\ntask-plans/operational-reliability-task-plan.md\n# Operational Reliability Task Plan\n\nStatus: complete\n\n## Priority\n\nPriority 1\n\n## Objective\n\nMake looping, background continue, and runtime status trustworthy.\n\n## Scope\n\n- detached background continue\n- loop observability\n- status semantics\n- degraded-state handling\n- log access and result visibility\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Task 1 — Background Continue Correctness\n\n---\ntask-plans/prompt-rule-memo-cards-task-plan.md\n# Prompt Rule Memo Cards Task Plan\n\n## Priority\n\nPriority 2\n\n## Objective\n\nTurn the extension into a working memory system, not only a launcher.\n\n## Scope\n\n- prompt cards\n- rule cards\n- memo cards\n- visibility of `prompt.md`, `ROADMAP.md`, and related loop files\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Task 1 — Card Types\n\n- define first-class card types for prompt, rule, memo\n- distinguish them visually from agent cards\n\n---\ntask-plans/publishable-product-quality-task-plan.md\n# Publishable Product Quality Task Plan\n\nStatus: complete\n\n## Priority\n\nPriority 1\n\n## Objective\n\nMake the extension's release path understandable, repeatable, and easier to evaluate directly from the repo.\n\n## Scope\n\n- screenshot / preview inventory\n- release posture and preview messaging\n- release notes and root-doc discoverability\n- package / publish validation path\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Task 1 — Screenshot Inventory\n\n- [x] define the minimum publishable screenshot set\n---\ntask-plans/wechat-bot-background-service-task-plan.md\n# WeChat Bot Background Service Task Plan\n\n## Priority\n\nPriority 4\n\n## Objective\n\nSupport durable background automation and external messaging through a service layer.\n\n## Scope\n\n- WeChat bot integration\n- background runtime\n- notification or task dispatch behavior\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Task 1 — Service Boundary\n\n- keep bot/service logic outside the VS Code extension host\n- define clear communication between extension and service\n\n### Task 2 — Bot Use Cases\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
